entry.title: [ios] Handle Incomplete Magic Stack Module Insertion Logic
entry.content:
In situations where the Magic Stack has already been initially created and a module needs to be added, modules ranked in front may not have

been added to the Magic Stack yet (more possible with dynamic

Segmentation ranking). It is not enough to map the literal index rank

of a module to the index it should be inserted into the Magic Stack.

Instead, it should use relative rank position to whatever module is already in the Magic Stack.

entry.title: [FPS] Use NetLog API unconditionally and more idiomatically
entry.content:
I took a look at the events in the netlog viewer (after finding

https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/HEAD/net/docs/crash-course-in-net-internals.md),

and learned there were better APIs for handling begin/end parts of a

single event. It also made it clear that the FPS metadata event didn't

need to include the request URL, since that's already recorded by the

parent URL_REQUEST_START_JOB event.



This CL also modifies the timing of the events so that they include

the round-trip for getting the cache filter info, since that is

unconditional.

entry.title: Consistently ClearPreviewedForm() before all filling operations.
entry.content:
Right now, ClearPreviewedForm() is only called before autofilling a

fields, not before autocompleting a field. This way, AutofillAgent::

previewed_elements_ is not reset in the autocomplete case. Since the

popup clears the form when it gets closed, slightly after filling

happened, this causes the filled field's AutofillState to get reset.

That makes the field lose its color, causing crbug.com/1478092.



This only started manifesting as a bug when crrev.com/c/4670896 landed

recently. Ultimately, the behavior can be considered buggy even before

the CL, since the agent retained no longer previewed elements in its

previewed_elements_ state.



This CL fixes this problem by calling ClearPreviewedForm() in every

case, which resets previewed_elements_ and resets all state tied

to the elements in Blink. As a result, when the popup calls

ClearPreviewedForm() again after filling, the operation is a no-op.

(Though clearing the form when the popup closes is legitimate if the

popup is closed while previewing something - so this should stay)



Fixed: 1478092

entry.title: Use a dynamic list of IP protection proxies
entry.content:
The primary purpose of this CL is to thread a list of proxy hostnames

through from `IpProtectionAuthTokenProvider` to the proxy delegate. This

list is cached for a long interval, but force-refreshed when proxies

fail. The result is minimal traffic to get the list during steady-state,

while allowing rapid changes to the list when necessary.



This brings a few related changes:



* `ProxyServer` gains an `is_for_ip_protection()` bit.

* `NetworkServiceProxyAllowList` provides a much simpler

`CustomProxyConfig`, which is largely ignored by the proxy

delegate when it is used for IP protection.

* Significant refactoring of `NetworkServiceProxyDelegate`.



In a followup, I will rename `IpProtectionAuthToken*` to `IpProtectionConfig*` since these classes do more than just handle auth tokens.

entry.title: Add `LayoutBox::MayHaveFragmentItems`
entry.content:
When creating `NGInlineCursor` without specifying the root

fragment, it needs to scan all fragments of the specified

`LayoutBlockFlow`. This can cause O(n^2) in pre-paint, when it

invalidates `LayoutBlockFlow`, not fragments, for each

fragment.



This patch adds `LayoutBox::MayHaveFragmentItems` that can

check the existence of `NGFragmentItems` quickly without

going through all fragments.



This improves `multicol/tall-content-short-columns.html` perf

test by 185%[1].

entry.title: Refactor LayoutSVGShape::UpdateShapeFromElement
entry.content:
Said method currently both updates the shape data, the object bounding

box, the stroke bounds and updates the non-scaling-stroke data.

Splitting this method up allows for more targeted updates to shape

properties (like not updating the shape when the stroke changes.)



Make UpdateShapeFromElement only handle updates of shape data and the

corresponding bounds (object bounding box). Updates of stroke bounds and

non-scaling-stroke is moved out to LayoutSVGShape::UpdateLayout.



UpdateShapeFromElement is also made pure virtual on LayoutSVGShape,

making it clear that subclasses should handle this operation.

(Subclasses now always use the same way to compute the objects bounds -

regardless of whether it uses a Path or not to represent the shape.)



Merge StrokeGeometryClass and ShapeGeometryCodePath into a new

SVGShapeGeometry which is set by UpdateShapeFromElement - either

explicitly or by inspecting the actual (Path) geometry.



Bug: 493888, 709437, 1393554

entry.title: [DBSC] Add subduration histograms for TPM operations
entry.content:
This CL adds two new histograms that gives a better visibility into

TPM operations latency.



Crypto.UnexportableKeys.BackgroundTaskDuration which reports the total

TPM operation is split into two sub-intervals: queue wait time and

execution time.



A little background on unexportable_keys::BackgroundLongTaskScheduler:

the scheduler maintains a queue of tasks on the UI thread and executes

them on the background thread one by one. These tasks are slow

(10-100ms) and non-parallelizable, so we want to have a better control

over the order in which they are executed.

info, and this may cause leaking. Run the listen success callback when

the info arrived to avoid the failure.

disconnect callback on state changed to prevent UI from listening the

same UUID while the previous one is not yet cleaned up.

entry.title: Revert "Remove SK_USE_LEGACY_BLUR_IMAGEFILTER staging flag"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 069d3d9db0b3093fec0edee412abfbdb9316f460.



Reason for revert: Linux MSan failures; see https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Linux%20MSan%20Tests/42742/overview.



Original change's description:

> Remove SK_USE_LEGACY_BLUR_IMAGEFILTER staging flag

>

> With the removal of this flag, CPU-based blurs will now respect the

> SkTileMode passed to the blur image filter. Both GPU and CPU blurs

> will tend to have more optimal image sizes (smaller) when using

> kDecal. kDecal should also use fewer renderpasses. There is a

> temporary regression in image size and renderpasses for other tile

> modes but this is a required step in the overall blur refactoring.

>

> It also fixes a bug where decal would be applied to the intersection

> of both the filter region and primitive subregion when performing

> blurs in SVGs. This is why there are larger changes to the

> `effect-reference-subregion`: the blur is able to read the hidden color cells of the input image, some of which are red so the overall blur color shifts from green to brownish.

>

> Most viz pixel tests have benign updates. However, the blur_filter_with_clip test is meant to have clamped content. The SW

> expected image had baked in the previous limitation of decal-only

> blurs which is no longer the case. However, the software_renderer

> compositor seems to be sizing images a little off so the clamp is only

> applying to the top and left edges. Now the new expected image is

> just half wrong :)

>

> Chromium is still relying on deprecated behavior for clamped blurs

> where it doesn't specify the clamping geometry with the image filter.

> This will require more changes but would likely get around the issue

> with how the software_renderer prepares the images to be blurred.

>

> Numerous ash pixel tests had to be updated, but I couldn't spot any

> meaningful differences in their content. My guess is that the widgets

> and windows all had some amount of blur use, so this change touched

> everywhere.

entry.title: Implement auto-pause/suspend behavior for SMIL animations
entry.content:
SMIL animations that run in hidden/invisible pages can yield bursts of

events when the page is made visible again. To alleviate this,

automatically suspend these animations for a bit to reduce the volume of

events a bit. Animations are suspended when a rAF-bound frame "lag" more

than a fixed limit of time (1 minute). To avoid suspending animations

which have event times that are spaced that far apart, make sure to

advance the "latest updated" time when handling non-rAF-bound updates.

longer a need to mention it, nor the possibility of specifying URLs with

term that appears elsewhere, and is commonly used in the industry now.

entry.title: Reland "vaapi: Remove usage of GL and libva-x11."
entry.content:
This reverts commit e26d31a8bb1642001e5db2e58d5b7e852adf4321.



Reason for revert: Underlying cause mitigated in CL:4790147



Original change's description:

> Revert "vaapi: Remove usage of GL and libva-x11."

>

> This reverts commit 7bc1edf3ef1d8ebb9c73bd5abe50299f7fe1f2c8.

>

> Reason for revert: Caused crbug.com/1466825

>

> Original change's description:

> > vaapi: Remove usage of GL and libva-x11.

> >

> > This CL removes the usage of GL stuff and the X11 libva API in the

> > VaapiWrapper in favor of always using libva-drm with no awareness of the

> > rendering API. This is possible now that we got rid of the legacy

> > VaapiVideoDecodeAccelerator code.

> >

> > This has a few benefits:

> >

> > 1) Simplifies the VADisplayStateSingleton initialization since we can

> > use the same path for ChromeOS and Linux.

> >

> > 2) VaapiWrapper won't know and won't care about whether we use GL,

> > Vulkan, ANGLE or any combination thereof. That's abstracted already

> > by the SharedImage framework.

> >

> > 3) It will make it easier to get Linux to work with out-of-process video

> > decoding (OOP-VD).

> >

> > Bug: 1326754

> > Test: HW decode acceleration works with CHROME_DEVEL_SANDBOX="${HOME}/chrome/chrome_sandbox" DISPLAY=:1.0 ~/chrome/chrome --user-data-dir=${HOME}/.chrome_dev_data --enable-features=VaapiVideoDecodeLinuxGL --disable-features=Vulkan --v=1 "https://crosvideo.appspot.com/?codec=h264&resolution=720&mute=true"
